Gemini Summary

Signal Summary:

  • The Housing Lead signal is currently in a Neutral regime, indicating stable housing activity with a composite score of 0.22 as of 2025-10-31 (1). This reflects a transition from earlier periods of contraction and expansion towards a more balanced state. Conviction Band: Medium, Interpretation Confidence: High Confidence, Internal Conflict Flag: Yes.

Key Dynamics:

  • Housing starts momentum (Z_HOUST: 0.82) is strong and positive, driving the signal towards expansion (1).
  • Conversely, building permits momentum (Z_PERMIT: -0.06) remains largely neutral, contributing little directional impetus (1).
  • Mortgage rates (Z_MORT: -0.20) continue to exert a modest headwind, though less restrictive than in previous periods (1).
  • Conditional Invalidation: A sustained composite Housing Lead score below -0.75 or above 0.75, leading to a definite "Contracting" or "Expanding" regime shift.

Scenario Balance:

  • Base Case dominant: Housing activity maintains its current neutral pace, with balancing pressures from strong starts and lingering mortgage rate headwinds.
  • Upside secondary: Housing activity could pick up if building permits also show strong positive momentum, or if mortgage rates decline significantly.
  • Downside residual: Housing activity could contract again if mortgage rates rise further, or if both permits and starts lose momentum.

Time Horizon & Aggregation:

  • Time Horizon: Cyclical (months). The signal captures momentum and cyclical turns in housing, which typically unfold over several months (1).
  • Aggregation Weight Hint: Medium. The signal provides a clear, quantitative assessment of housing cycles, but current mixed internal dynamics suggest it should be balanced with other growth indicators.

Macro Relevance:

  • Macro dimension informed: Demand (consumer and investment), credit conditions, and overall growth (1).
  • Cycle position: Mid-cycle, reflecting a period of stabilisation after earlier volatility.
  • Typical interaction with other macro signals: Often leads broader economic cycles and is sensitive to changes in credit conditions (1) and consumer sentiment (2).

Data & References:

  • Building Permits (PERMIT) - latest 1428.0 (2025-10-31) (1).
  • Housing Starts (HOUST) - latest 1352.0 (2025-10-31) (1).
  • 30-Year Fixed Rate Mortgage Average (MORTGAGE30US) - latest 6.72 (2025-10-31) (1).
  • Additional public datasets: Consumer Sentiment (2) and Credit Conditions Signal (3) would enhance reliability regarding demand-side drivers and affordability.
